## Common Error Scenarios

| Scenario                                         | Status Code | Error Type         | Message                                                          |
|--------------------------------------------------|------------|--------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Missing, Invalid or Expired access token         | 401        | -                  | <code style={{ background: "#f8d7da", color: "#721c24", padding: "4px 8px", borderRadius: "5px" }}>Exception while fetching data: Denied.</code> |
| Missing allowed roles                            | 200        | PERMISSION_DENIED  | <code style={{ background: "#f8d7da", color: "#721c24", padding: "4px 8px", borderRadius: "5px" }}>Missing Request Parameters</code> |
| Input Parameters - null                          | 200        | BAD_REQUEST        | <code style={{ background: "#f8d7da", color: "#721c24", padding: "4px 8px", borderRadius: "5px" }}>Invalid Request</code> |
| Input Parameter - invalid                        | 200        | BAD_REQUEST        | <code style={{ background: "#f8d7da", color: "#721c24", padding: "4px 8px", borderRadius: "5px" }}>The upstream service is experiencing an issue. Please try again.</code> |
| Server Errors from External Service (5xx)        | 200        | INTERNAL           | <code style={{ background: "#f8d7da", color: "#721c24", padding: "4px 8px", borderRadius: "5px" }}>Client Error from External Service.</code> |
| Client Errors from External Service (4xx)        | 200        | INTERNAL           | <code style={{ background: "#f8d7da", color: "#721c24", padding: "4px 8px", borderRadius: "5px" }}>Exception while fetching data</code> |

